# Tmux

## Reloading

    tmux source-file ~/.tmux.conf

## Moving windows

    swap-window -s SOURCE_INDEX -t TARGET_INDEX

### Examples:

To move window number 3 to the beginning of the stack (assuming the stack index starts with 1 and not 0):

    swap-window -s 3 -t 1

The `-s` option can be omitted if the source window is the currently active one:

    swap-window -t 1

### Key binding:

Move the current window to the beginning when `<CTRL-b><T>` are pressed:

    bind-key T swap-window -t 1
